Ext.data.JsonP['Android_Menu']({"guide":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?>\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n    <title>Android Menu</title>\n\n    <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n    <meta content=\"Scroll EclipseHelp Exporter\" name=\"generator\">\n\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" media=\"print\">\n</link></link></link></meta></meta></head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n\t\t<div id=\"banner\" class=\"confbox admonition admonition-note aui-message warning shadowed information-macro\">\n\t\t\t<p>You can now find Appcelerator documentation at <a href=\"https://docs.axway.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://docs.axway.com/</a>. This site will be taken down in the near future.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n        <div class=\"header\"/>\n\n        <div id=\"src-41845737\" class=\"content\">\n                        <h1>Android Menu</h1>\n    <p>Demonstrates basic use of Menu and MenuItem objects to display items in the Android action bar.    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox admonition admonition-info aui-message hint shadowed information-macro has-no-icon\">\n            <div class=\"title\">App Folder Location</div>\n            <p>alloy/test/apps/<strong class=\" \">ui/android_menu</strong>    </p>\n    </div>\n        <p>    <span style=\"color: #222222;\">\nThe <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Android.Menu\">Menu</a> and <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Android.Menu\">MenuItem</a> elements let you add items to the Android <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"http://developer.android.com/guide/topics/ui/actionbar.html\" target=\"_blank\">action bar</a>,     <span style=\"color: #222222;\">\na window feature that identifies the user location, and provides user actions and navigation modes.    </span>\n    </span>\n    </p>\n    <p>    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/41845737/screenshot.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/41845737/screenshot.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" width=\"250\">\n        </img></p>\n    <div class=\"confbox programlisting defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n                    <div class=\"title\">app/views/index.xml</div>\n                <div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" class=\"defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\" data-title=\"app/views/index.xml\">\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">&lt;Alloy&gt;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">    &lt;Window&gt;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">        &lt;ActionBar id=</code><code class=\"string\">&quot;actionbar&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\"> title=</code><code class=\"string\">&quot;My XML Menu&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\"> /&gt;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">        &lt;!-- This will add an Android menu --&gt;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">        &lt;Menu&gt;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">            &lt;MenuItem title=</code><code class=\"string\">&quot;option 1&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\"> icon=</code><code class=\"string\">&quot;/ic_menu_help.png&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\"> onClick=</code><code class=\"string\">&quot;doClick&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\">/&gt;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">            &lt;MenuItem title=</code><code class=\"string\">&quot;option 2&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\"> icon=</code><code class=\"string\">&quot;/ic_menu_home.png&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\"> onClick=</code><code class=\"string\">&quot;openWin2&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\">/&gt;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">        &lt;/Menu&gt;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">        </code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">        &lt;!-- Build the rest of your UI as usual --&gt;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">        &lt;Label&gt;Window </code><code class=\"value\">1</code><code class=\"plain\">&lt;/Label&gt;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">        &lt;Label bottom=</code><code class=\"string\">&quot;20dp&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\">&gt;Press the menu button&lt;/Label&gt;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">    &lt;/Window&gt;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">&lt;/Alloy&gt;</code></div>\n</div>\n    </div>\n    <p>The &quot;option 1&quot; and &quot;option 2&quot; MenuItem elements contains <tt class=\" \">onClick</tt> attributes that define functions, <tt class=\" \">doClick()</tt> and <tt class=\" \">openWin2()</tt>, that are invoked when selected.    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox programlisting defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n                    <div class=\"title\">app/controllers/index.js</div>\n                <div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" class=\"defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\" data-title=\"app/controllers/index.js\">\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">function doClick(e) {</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">    alert(e.source.title);</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">}</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">function openWin2(e) {</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">    Alloy.createController(</code><code class=\"string\">&apos;win2&apos;</code><code class=\"plain\">).getView().open();</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">}</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">$.index.open();</code></div>\n</div>\n    </div>\n    <p>The first option displays an alert dialog, and the second opens the window defined by app/views/win2.xml, which requires another Menu and MenuItem objects defined by app/views/menu.xml.    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox programlisting defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n                    <div class=\"title\">app/views/menu.xml</div>\n                <div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" class=\"defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\" data-title=\"app/views/menu.xml\">\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">&lt;Alloy&gt;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">    &lt;Menu&gt;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">        &lt;MenuItem title=</code><code class=\"string\">&quot;require 1&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\"> icon=</code><code class=\"string\">&quot;/ic_menu_goto.png&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\"> onClick=</code><code class=\"string\">&quot;doClick&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\">/&gt;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">        &lt;MenuItem title=</code><code class=\"string\">&quot;require 2&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\"> icon=</code><code class=\"string\">&quot;/ic_menu_manage.png&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\"> onClick=</code><code class=\"string\">&quot;doClick&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\">/&gt;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">    &lt;/Menu&gt;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">&lt;/Alloy&gt;</code></div>\n</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"confbox admonition admonition-info aui-message hint shadowed information-macro\">\n            <p>Before Android 3.0 (Honeycomb), all Android devices included a dedicated Menu button used to display the options menu panel populated by MenuItem objects. New Android devices do not include such a dedicated menu button and Google has encouraged developers to use the action bar instead. The following screenshot shows the same test application running on an Android 2.3.3 simulator.    </p>\n    <p>    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/41845737/menu_233.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/41845737/menu_233.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" width=\"250\">\n        </img></p>\n    </div>\n        <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-41845737_AndroidMenu-SeeAlso\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>See Also</span></h2>\n<ul class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Android.Menu\">Titanium.Android.Menu</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Android.MenuItem\">Titanium.Android.MenuItem</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"#!/api/Titanium.Android.ActionBar\">Titanium.Android.ActionBar</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"http://android-developers.blogspot.com/2012/01/say-goodbye-to-menu-button.html\" target=\"_blank\">Say Goodbye to the Menu Button</a> (Android Developer Blog)    </p>\n</li></ul>    <p>    </p>\n    <p>    </p>\n    </div>\n        </div><a id=\"editButton\" href=\"https://wiki.appcelerator.org/pages/editpage.action?pageId=41845737\"><span>Edit</span></a>\n    \n        \n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","title":"Android Menu"});